instanceof and is(true) isnt the best way to do this - if this fails, then you wont know what the actual type was. Change to 

assertThat(srvDetailsSrvProvided, instanceOf(ServiceDetailsServiceProvided.class));
assertThat(srvDetailsSrvProvided, not(instanceOf(ServiceDetailsServiceProvided.class)));

I know this was a temp workaround, but if we are putting this in long term, I think we could try to do this in more generic manner. Shouldnt we be doing this for every call to Navigation.logout()?

IMO we should overload Navigation.logout() to accept a validationCloseButton so that its easy to call.

public static void logout(final WebDriver driver, Button validationCloseButton) {
    validationCloseButton.click();
    // Do normal logout
}

Alternatively, we could update the existing logout logic to first navigate to the homepage, and then click logout, meaning there would be no validations, as you are on the home page (you may need to take care to close any popup).

